    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gourd family of flowering plants, containing 98 genera and about 975 species of food and ornamental plants. Members of the family are annual or perennial herbs native to temperate and tropical areas and include cucumbers, gourds, melons, squashes, and pumpkins.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
